15
00:00:51,843 --> 00:00:53,971
[Snoring lightly]

16
00:01:09,194 --> 00:01:12,698
Oh, it's you.

17
00:01:14,199 --> 00:01:15,158
Meh.

18
00:01:15,200 --> 00:01:16,827
Meh.

19
00:01:23,667 --> 00:01:27,087
[Slow motion]
Hi, everyone!

20
00:01:31,341 --> 00:01:35,095
My babies!

21
00:01:38,307 --> 00:01:41,602
[Power saw whirring]

22
00:01:41,602 --> 00:01:44,855
[Crickets chirping]

23
00:01:44,938 --> 00:01:46,607
Mashed potato?

24
00:01:48,233 --> 00:01:49,860
Pie pie?

25
00:01:49,860 --> 00:01:51,445
[Shoring]

26
00:01:59,745 --> 00:02:01,872
[Snoring lightly]

27
00:02:01,872 --> 00:02:03,624
TREE TRUNKS: [Laughs]

28
00:02:03,707 --> 00:02:05,125
Okay, bye!

29
00:02:06,251 --> 00:02:07,711
Hey, where'd you go?

30
00:02:07,753 --> 00:02:11,548
I think I was visited
by aliens again.

31
00:02:11,548 --> 00:02:17,804
Every few years, they stop by
and show me my hybrid children.

32
00:02:17,929 --> 00:02:19,389
[Laughs] What?

33
00:02:19,431 --> 00:02:24,436
Don't be jealous
of my alien consorts, Mr. Pig.

34
00:02:24,436 --> 00:02:27,064
I love you the most.

35
00:02:27,147 --> 00:02:29,900
[Chuckles]
All right, sweetie. Thank you.

36
00:02:29,941 --> 00:02:31,151
[Smooches]

37
00:02:31,193 --> 00:02:32,319
You gonna come with me

38
00:02:32,402 --> 00:02:34,821
to Princess Bubblegum's
fireworks show tomorrow?

39
00:02:34,821 --> 00:02:37,449
No, she vvizzed on our wedding.

40
00:02:37,532 --> 00:02:41,286
I'm sorry, but she's
a fat fish in the sand.

41
00:02:41,328 --> 00:02:43,580
I want to see
free fireworks, though,

42
00:02:43,580 --> 00:02:45,540
and I want you to come with me.

43
00:02:45,540 --> 00:02:47,542
Eh, all right.

44
00:02:47,584 --> 00:02:48,794
[Smack! Squeal!]

45
00:02:50,212 --> 00:02:53,298
[Up-tempo music playing]

46
00:03:01,098 --> 00:03:02,599
[Music stops]

47
00:03:02,599 --> 00:03:04,351
Science rules!

48
00:03:05,185 --> 00:03:06,728
Here's some proof.

49
00:03:10,190 --> 00:03:12,067
[Camera shutter clicking]

50
00:03:13,985 --> 00:03:16,113
I'm doing the right thing.

51
00:03:17,447 --> 00:03:19,491
[Warbling]

52
00:03:21,201 --> 00:03:22,953
Free fireworks!

53
00:03:22,994 --> 00:03:25,455
Right! Here we go!

54
00:03:25,497 --> 00:03:27,749
[Applause]

55
00:03:28,959 --> 00:03:30,877
[Whirl]

56
00:03:32,254 --> 00:03:35,090
[Whistle!]

57
00:03:35,132 --> 00:03:37,217
[Laughing]
Whoa-ho-ho-ho! Whoa!

58
00:03:37,259 --> 00:03:39,469
Whoa-ho-ho!

59
00:03:39,511 --> 00:03:41,096
Hey, where's my wife?

60
00:03:44,641 --> 00:03:47,227
[Slow motion] What's that?

61
00:03:47,269 --> 00:03:48,895
Meh.

62
00:03:52,274 --> 00:03:54,025
[Hiss!]

63
00:03:55,402 --> 00:03:58,029
[Chattering]

64
00:04:01,283 --> 00:04:03,285
[Beatboxes techno beat]

65
00:04:03,285 --> 00:04:06,371
Oh!

66
00:04:10,792 --> 00:04:16,339
Hey, you blind, cream-faced,
lonely lighthouse keeper.

67
00:04:16,381 --> 00:04:19,217
Stop hurting my space men
with your goo!

68
00:04:19,259 --> 00:04:20,761
What?
How did you --

69
00:04:20,844 --> 00:04:24,765
Keep your probes
out of my star children.

70
00:04:25,849 --> 00:04:27,851
Tree Trunks, you don't know
what you're talking about.

71
00:04:27,893 --> 00:04:30,145
TREE TRUNKS:
Don't you condescend to me,

72
00:04:30,270 --> 00:04:32,272
you false idol.

73
00:04:32,397 --> 00:04:35,776
You probed the wrong famiglia!

74
00:04:40,906 --> 00:04:43,492
[Twinkle!]

75
00:04:44,534 --> 00:04:45,660
Wake up.

76
00:04:45,786 --> 00:04:48,747
The fireworks show
is a secret space war.

77
00:04:48,789 --> 00:04:51,541
Get your goo out of my UFO.

78
00:04:51,541 --> 00:04:52,918
Dude, this town
is full of kooks.

79
00:04:55,879 --> 00:04:58,924
Save the galactic chitlins!

80
00:04:58,924 --> 00:05:00,258
Oh!

81
00:05:01,259 --> 00:05:05,806
"Meet Starchy
in that alley over there."

82
00:05:10,811 --> 00:05:13,814
Cacaw! Cacaw!

83
00:05:13,814 --> 00:05:16,650
I'll just ask this duck.

84
00:05:16,691 --> 00:05:18,902
Excuse me, but --

85
00:05:18,944 --> 00:05:20,570
STARCHY:
Don't be alarmed.

86
00:05:20,654 --> 00:05:23,073
I am the disembodied voice
of the people,

87
00:05:23,156 --> 00:05:25,534
and I have witnessed your fire.

88
00:05:25,575 --> 00:05:27,661
If given the opportunity,

89
00:05:27,702 --> 00:05:30,330
would you lead a small group
of resistance fighters

90
00:05:30,413 --> 00:05:32,040
straight into the hornet's den?

91
00:05:32,040 --> 00:05:35,210
You bet your wet booty.

92
00:05:35,293 --> 00:05:37,587
Behold!
It's me, Starchy!

93
00:05:37,671 --> 00:05:38,922
Oh.

94
00:05:38,964 --> 00:05:40,215
[Whirl]

95
00:05:40,215 --> 00:05:42,425
BOTH: Aaaaah!

96
00:05:42,467 --> 00:05:43,593
Unh!

97
00:05:43,593 --> 00:05:45,470
Starchy always screams.

98
00:05:45,595 --> 00:05:49,975
TREE TRUNKS:
This is very elaborate!

99
00:06:03,363 --> 00:06:05,115
Hello, everyone.

100
00:06:05,198 --> 00:06:07,576
We have a new member
with us here tonight.

101
00:06:07,617 --> 00:06:09,744
Please welcome Train Tracks.

102
00:06:09,870 --> 00:06:12,247
ALL:
Welcome, Train Tracks!

103
00:06:12,330 --> 00:06:14,583
Clap! Clap! Clap!
Clap! Clap! Clap! Clap!

104
00:06:14,624 --> 00:06:16,751
Veritas Brigade!

105
00:06:16,751 --> 00:06:20,255
Train Tracks has her own
incredible story to tell,

106
00:06:20,380 --> 00:06:21,590
so let's let her talk.

107
00:06:21,631 --> 00:06:22,507
Hi, Train Tracks.

108
00:06:22,591 --> 00:06:25,886
lam a conduit for
an alien entity known as Booshy.

109
00:06:26,011 --> 00:06:28,763
There's a 50/50 chance that
Booshy will speak through me

110
00:06:28,847 --> 00:06:29,764
during this meeting.

111
00:06:29,848 --> 00:06:31,516
[Gasps]
Oh, my gosh, it's happening.

112
00:06:31,516 --> 00:06:32,767
[Grunting]

113
00:06:32,851 --> 00:06:35,270
I love when Booshy shows up.

114
00:06:35,353 --> 00:06:37,898
F-- F-- F--

115
00:06:37,898 --> 00:06:40,233
[Deep voice]
It's Booshy. Hello!

116
00:06:40,275 --> 00:06:42,402
ALL:
Welcome, Booshy.

117
00:06:42,485 --> 00:06:46,114
On my planet, we speak in colors
instead of words.

118
00:06:46,156 --> 00:06:47,532
Aw, stuff it, Booshy.

119
00:06:47,616 --> 00:06:50,410
We've got a real experiencer
in our midst.

120
00:06:52,621 --> 00:06:54,915
[Clicking tongue]

121
00:06:57,292 --> 00:06:59,502
Do y'all have any guns?

122
00:06:59,544 --> 00:07:00,420
Nope.

123
00:07:00,503 --> 00:07:02,422
Raaah!

124
00:07:02,505 --> 00:07:07,552
I don't have time
for campfire stories.

125
00:07:07,636 --> 00:07:11,306
I'm a mother of six,
and they're in trouble

126
00:07:11,389 --> 00:07:14,267
because Princess Bubblegum's
probing them.

127
00:07:14,309 --> 00:07:17,687
Will you help me raise a ruckus?

128
00:07:17,771 --> 00:07:19,814
ALL:
Of course we will!

129
00:07:19,814 --> 00:07:22,442
Let's stink it up!

130
00:07:39,584 --> 00:07:41,586
What in the --

131
00:07:47,425 --> 00:07:49,678
Oh, my gracious.

132
00:07:49,719 --> 00:07:54,099
A full-scale galactic invasion?

133
00:07:54,182 --> 00:07:59,104
Well, let's see how well you fly
without your thing.

134
00:07:59,104 --> 00:08:00,730
Aaaah!

135
00:08:00,855 --> 00:08:02,732
[Whirl]

136
00:08:02,816 --> 00:08:04,943
Oh, good night!

137
00:08:09,489 --> 00:08:13,076
You're the devil's
hot little helpers.

138
00:08:13,118 --> 00:08:15,245
Come get extinguished!

139
00:08:15,370 --> 00:08:17,580
BUBBLEGUM:
What the funge, Tree Trunks?!

140
00:08:21,001 --> 00:08:23,378
Girl,
you just crossed the big line!

141
00:08:23,461 --> 00:08:26,506
Well, this is the people's
justi-i-i-

142
00:08:26,589 --> 00:08:27,716
Holy!

143
00:08:27,757 --> 00:08:29,718
...i-1-ice.

144
00:08:30,468 --> 00:08:34,180
[Slow motion]
What should I do?

145
00:08:41,938 --> 00:08:45,025
Booshy's only prison
is this wicked planet.

146
00:08:45,066 --> 00:08:46,901
Yeah, well, join the club.

147
00:08:46,943 --> 00:08:49,279
[Whirl]

148
00:08:52,449 --> 00:08:53,950
[Slow motion] What?

149
00:08:54,075 --> 00:08:55,660
Tree Trunks!

150
00:08:55,785 --> 00:08:58,079
What is this place?

151
00:08:58,079 --> 00:09:01,291
You already know.

152
00:09:03,084 --> 00:09:07,464
[Gasps]

153
00:09:12,677 --> 00:09:14,971
TREE TRUNKS: See?

154
00:09:15,597 --> 00:09:19,726
They refuse to fight back.

155
00:09:23,855 --> 00:09:26,232
[Retching]

156
00:09:30,445 --> 00:09:32,363
[Grunts] What?

157
00:09:32,447 --> 00:09:34,491
What?! What?!!

158
00:09:34,491 --> 00:09:36,242
See, I told you.

159
00:09:36,242 --> 00:09:37,619
What?!

160
00:09:37,619 --> 00:09:39,621
Space men.

161
00:09:40,371 --> 00:09:42,082
I'm really sorry, Tree Trunks.

162
00:09:42,123 --> 00:09:45,376
I never meant to hurt anybody
with my space program.

163
00:09:45,502 --> 00:09:47,712
It was supposed to seed
new candy kingdoms

164
00:09:47,754 --> 00:09:49,506
on uninhabited planets

165
00:09:49,506 --> 00:09:52,383
in case Ooo0 goes
straight-up dongbongles.

166
00:09:52,509 --> 00:09:54,636
'Cause, like, confidentially,

167
00:09:54,719 --> 00:09:56,596
there's a lot of ways
that could happen.

168
00:09:56,638 --> 00:09:58,264
And when it does,

169
00:09:58,264 --> 00:10:01,851
maybe I won't look so crazy
after all, you know?

170
00:10:01,893 --> 00:10:05,355
I can help you find
a space for your goo.

171
00:10:06,272 --> 00:10:07,899
You would do that?

172
00:10:07,982 --> 00:10:11,027
You and I will never be friends,

173
00:10:11,152 --> 00:10:13,988
but we can respect each other
as mothers

174
00:10:14,030 --> 00:10:15,782
and as fellow believers

175
00:10:15,907 --> 00:10:20,662
in the infinite promise
of the cosmos above.

176
00:10:20,662 --> 00:10:21,621
Sure.

177
00:10:21,663 --> 00:10:23,164
[Crickets chirping]

178
00:10:26,042 --> 00:10:28,795
Oh, hello, darling.

179
00:10:28,878 --> 00:10:30,421
Hello.

180
00:10:30,547 --> 00:10:32,549
You can talk?

181
00:10:32,549 --> 00:10:35,510
Yeah, there are websites
that teach you.

182
00:10:35,552 --> 00:10:37,887
I wanted to tell you
that I did what you said.

183
00:10:37,929 --> 00:10:40,306
We're going to fly
Princess Bubblegum's probes

184
00:10:40,431 --> 00:10:42,392
back to our abandoned
home planet.

185
00:10:42,433 --> 00:10:43,810
They'll have
all the space they need

186
00:10:43,935 --> 00:10:45,812
to start
their new Candy Kingdom.

187
00:10:45,895 --> 00:10:47,897
But our galaxy is so far away,

188
00:10:47,939 --> 00:10:51,442
I won't see you again
for at least 40 years.

189
00:10:52,068 --> 00:10:55,196
Take care of our alien babies.

190
00:10:55,280 --> 00:10:57,407
Who the slop is this?!

191
00:10:57,448 --> 00:10:59,784
This is my alien husband.

192
00:11:06,833 --> 00:11:10,962
s Come along with me J

193
00:11:11,045 --> 00:11:15,175
J And the butterflies and bees &

194
00:11:18,219 --> 00:11:20,346
This party is so crazy!

